title: Chinese art of the warring states period 480-222 BC (Art Ebook)
description:
Chinese Art of the Warring States Period: Change and Continuity, 480-222 B.C.
Freer Gallery of Art | 1983 | 0934686394 | English | 212 pages | PDF | 22 MB

This is a catalog of the above collection from the Freer Gallery of Art in Washington DC. There are preliminary chapters on the historical background to the period. The remainder is devoted to heavily described illustrations of the collection, beginning with bronze vessels, fittings and weapons of the period; bronze mirrors, bronze garment hooks, jades, and lacquer ware. More than 138 items are included and illustrated
